The paper deals with the problem of finding anomalies in high-dimensional data using PCA based anomaly scores. This problem is closely related to machine learning and data mining, which are covered by the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. The paper also involves the use of matrix sketching techniques, which are related to data structures and algorithms, covered by the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. The paper also involves the use of matrix perturbation inequalities, which are related to information theory, covered by the cs.IT (Information Theory) sub-category. The paper also involves the use of random projections, which are related to computer vision, covered by the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the use of efficient algorithms, which are related to numerical analysis, covered by the cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) sub-category.
